<h2>HVAC Systems for Hillsboro</h2>

<p>Hillsboro's marine climate creates unique HVAC requirements that differ from other regions. The moderate temperatures mean homeowners don't need the highest-efficiency systems, but humidity control becomes more important during the wet winter months. For air conditioning, a SEER rating of 14-16 is typically sufficient for Hillsboro's mild summers, where temperatures rarely exceed 90¬∞F for extended periods. Heat pumps are particularly well-suited for this climate, as they can efficiently provide both heating and cooling while performing optimally in the moderate temperature ranges common to the area.</p>

<p>For heating systems, ductless mini-split heat pumps or high-efficiency gas furnaces work best in Hillsboro homes. Mini-splits offer zoned comfort control, which is perfect for the city's diverse home layouts and can reduce energy consumption by 30-40% compared to traditional central systems. Gas furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher are also excellent choices, especially when paired with smart thermostats that can optimize heating schedules based on Hillsboro's predictable weather patterns. Proper humidity control through whole-home dehumidifiers or ventilation systems is crucial during the wet season to prevent moisture issues and maintain indoor air quality.</p>

<h2>Hillsboro Energy Incentives</h2>

<p>Hillsboro homeowners have access to several valuable incentives for solar and HVAC installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on solar panel system costs through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Oregon offers additional state incentives, including the Residential Energy Tax Credit, which can provide up to \$6,000 in credits for solar installations and energy-efficient HVAC systems. The state also has a net metering program that allows solar customers to receive retail rate credits for excess energy production.</p>

<p>PGE offers several rebate programs for energy-efficient home improvements. Their Clean Wind program allows customers to support renewable energy, while rebates are available for high-efficiency heat pumps, smart thermostats, and ductless mini-split systems. Washington County sometimes provides additional local incentives for renewable energy installations. Many Hillsboro residents can also take advantage of PACE financing programs, which allow property owners to finance solar and energy efficiency improvements through property tax assessments, spreading costs over 10-20 years with no upfront payment required.</p>

