<p>Downtown Hillsboro's urban core presents unique challenges and opportunities, with townhomes and condos requiring creative solar solutions like shared solar gardens or building-integrated systems. The established neighborhoods near Jackson Bottom Wetlands Preserve often feature older homes that can benefit significantly from both solar installations and HVAC upgrades, as these properties typically have higher energy consumption. Areas near Nike's headquarters and other tech companies tend to have environmentally conscious residents who are early adopters of solar technology, creating supportive communities for renewable energy investments.</p>

